title.Value: Julien Dufresne - 2013 FIS Nor-AM - Stratton - Day 2 - Mens Qualification

description.Name: description
description.Value: The Mens Qualification run by Julien Dufresne on Day 2 Duals of the 2013 FIS Freestyle North American Cup Mogul Skiing Competition on the infamous World Cup run at Stratton Mountain, Vermont, United States. The final day of Competition for the 2013 FIS Freestyle North American Cup Mogul Tour was intense, with 6 male and 6 female athletes still in the hunt for their respective Tour Title. The eventual tour winners were Bruce Perry Junior and Ali Kariotis, both from the United States of America, who both proved to be the most competitive and consistent skiers on the 2013 FIS Freestyle North American Cup Mogul Tour. The event hosted the top mogul skiing athletes from teams across the United States and Canada as well as athletes competing for Japan and Australian Mogul Skiing athletes from the New South Wales Institute of Sport (NSWIS) and the Mogul Skiing Academy (AUSMSA). Check out www.mogulskiingacademy.com/videos for more videos from the event.
